  <title>Bell Crank</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Bell-Crank</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Popup Box"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:180px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><image src="MD-Bell-Crank.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title>Image of Bell Crank</title></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A Bell-Crank is a Part that is usually connected to the Base-Part with a Pin-Joint, at a so-called &apos;fulcrum&apos;. Two levers radiate from the fulcrum, each with a Pin-Joint at its end. The angle between the two levers is usually 90º.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The lengths of the levers control if the Bell Crank amplifies or attenuates the motion. </para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">To draw a Bell-Crank: Add one Part<image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%"></image>, Joint it to the Base-Part<image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%"></image>, the other end of the Part and one Pin-Joint<image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%"></image> of the Bell-Crank) Edit the Part, and add a Line<image src="Red-14-4.gif" scale="100.00%"></image> from the origin<image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%"></image> to where you want the other Pin-Joint<image src="Red-14-5.gif" scale="100.00%"></image>, Close the Part-Editor. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The sketch-loop<image src="Red-14-6.gif" scale="100.00%"></image> is optional.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
